<title>Customs at death</title>
<summary>Tamme&apos;s younger brother dies so his mother sleeps outside at the back of the house. When a child dies, another child does not eat. Another child also &apos;must die&apos;. When a person dies the people bury him or her in the earth.</summary><comments>1) See also <i>Sleeping in ashes</i> and <i>Burial</i> and <i>Burial (another account)</i>, 2) This story is found in Book XI &amp; XII-3</comments><date>4-5 January 1879</date><storypages>9212-9215</storypages><category>History (personal)</category><category>Custom and daily life</category><author>Tamme (XII)</author><keyword><kw>death</kw><subkw>!kun customs at</subkw></keyword>
